# Title: Potential Signing Bypass Via Windows Developer Features
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2023-01-11
# Level: high
# Description: Detects when a user enable developer features such as "Developer Mode" or "Application Sideloading". Which allows the user to install untrusted packages.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.stealth
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_systemsettingsadminflows_turn_on_dev_features.yml

CommandLine="*TurnOnDeveloperFeatures*" Image="*\\SystemSettingsAdminFlows.exe" OR OriginalFileName="SystemSettingsAdminFlows.EXE" CommandLine IN ("*DeveloperUnlock*", "*EnableSideloading*")